Pre-activation behavior: <code>OP_OPTX_KNOT</code> and <code>OP_OPTX_KNOT_VERIFY</code> always consume their three stack items (<code><spatial_sig></code>, <code><knot_data></code>, <code><pubkey></code>) and push TRUE. This ensures identical stack state between upgraded and non-upgraded nodes. Stack items are consumed unconditionally; only the cryptographic verification is gated by the activation flag. This follows the same soft-fork pattern as OP_CHECKLOCKTIMEVERIFY (BIP-65).

Post-activation: full knot invariant verification is enforced. Invalid proofs cause the opcode to push FALSE (<code>OP_OPTX_KNOT</code>) or fail the script (<code>OP_OPTX_KNOT_VERIFY</code>).

===Script Verification Flag===

<code>SCRIPT_VERIFY_OPTX_KNOT</code> (bit 22) controls whether knot proof verification is performed. When unset, the opcodes act as NOP.

==Security Considerations==

===Composite Hardness (Theorem 1, GENSYS v2.2.2)===

Breaking OPTX requires either:

# Solving MLWE/MSIS (breaking ML-DSA), OR
# Computing a non-trivial isotopy invariant of K without knowledge of the DT code (solving the unknotting decision problem)

Since no polynomial-time quantum algorithm is known for (2), and (1) is assumed hard under standard lattice assumptions, OPTX achieves composite post-quantum security.

===Witness Malleability===

Braid words admit multiple representations for the same knot (Reidemeister moves, Markov moves). The spatial signature commits to a canonical braid form (Garside normal form) and the SHA-256 commitment covers the full invariant suite, preventing witness mutation that preserves validity.

===DoS via Polynomial Computation===

HOMFLY-PT polynomial computation is #P-hard in general. The MAX_OPTX_CROSSINGS bound (16) ensures worst-case evaluation remains bounded. The validation weight cost (750) provides economic DoS protection via fee markets.

===AGT Tensor Replay===

The AGT biometric binding is cryptographically bound to the transaction sighash, preventing replay of captured gaze tensors across transactions.

==Backwards Compatibility==

Pre-activation, the opcodes consume stack items and push TRUE, producing identical stack state on upgraded and non-upgraded nodes. This is the standard BIP-9 soft-fork NOP-expansion pattern used by BIP-65 (OP_CHECKLOCKTIMEVERIFY) and BIP-112 (OP_CHECKSEQUENCEVERIFY).

No existing transactions use opcodes 0xc0 or 0xc1. The opcodes are drawn from the reserved NOP range.

